<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Precautions Section</title>
  <style>
body {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  background-color: green;
}

.precautions-section {
padding: 60px 20px;
background-color: rgba(235, 236, 235, 0.9);
width:100%;
}

.precautions-section h2 {
text-align: center;
color:  rgba(2, 13, 0, 0.85);
font-size: 36px;
margin-bottom: 40px;
padding: 20px 40px;
text-decoration: underline;
  
}

.precautions-grid {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));  /* 4 equal columns */
gap: 150px;
width: 100%;
max-width: 1200px;
margin: 0 auto;           /* ✅ centers the grid */
padding: 0 20px;          /* equal spacing on both sides */
box-sizing: border-box;  /* ensures padding doesn’t break layout */
}

.precaution-card {     
 background: #ffffff;
  border-radius: 16px;
  box-shadow: 0 6px 24px rgba(37, 32, 32, 0.06);
  padding: 40px 20px;
  text-align: center;
  transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  width: 30vh;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.precaution-card:hover {
transform: translateY(-5px);
}
.precaution-card img {
  width: 250px;   /* Increased from 60px */
  height: 250px;
  display: block;
  margin: 0 auto 20px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.precaution-card h4 {
font-size: 22px;
color: #093252;
 margin-bottom: 10px;
 text-decoration: underline;
}

.precaution-card p {
font-size: 15px;
color: black;
line-height: 1.5;
}

 @media (max-width: 600px) {
.precautions-section h2 {
 font-size: 24px;
}
}
    
.precaution-group-title {
  font-size: 32px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #145DA0; /* Deep blue - calm and clinical */
  text-align: center;
  margin: 80px 0 40px;
  position: relative;
  padding-bottom: 12px;
  font-family: 'Poppins', 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  text-decoration: underline;
}

.precaution-group-title::after {
  position: absolute;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  bottom: 0;
  width: 80px;
  height: 4px;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #50b3d8, #85d8ce);
  border-radius: 2px;
}
.precaution-section-title {
  font-size: 40px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #145DA0;
  margin: 0;
  font-family: 'Poppins', 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  position: relative;
  padding-bottom: 12px;
}

.precaution-section-title::after {
  position: absolute;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  bottom: 0;
  width: 100px;
  height: 4px;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #50b3d8, #85d8ce);
  border-radius: 2px;
}
@media (max-width: 992px) {
  .precautions-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    padding: 0 20px;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .precautions-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    padding: 0 15px;
  }
}
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .precautions-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
  }

  .precaution-section-title {
    font-size: 28px;
  }

  .precaution-group-title {
    font-size: 24px;
  }
}
</style>
</head>

<body>
<section class="precautions-section">
<h2 class="precaution-section-title">Disease Prevention & Safety Precautions</h2>
 <!-- Nutritional Deficiencies -->
<h3 class="precaution-group-title">Nutritional Deficiencies</h3>
<div class="precautions-grid">
  <!-- Anemia -->
  <div class="precaution-card">
   <img src="https://plus.unsplash.com/premium_photo-1673214880615-c22716401a78?w=400&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8MXx8YW5lbWlhfGVufDB8fDB8fHww" alt="Vitamin C Icon" /> 
    <h4>Prevent Anemia</h4>
    <p>Anemia is a condition where your body lacks enough healthy red blood cells or hemoglobin to carry adequate oxygen to your tissues. This leads to fatigue and weakness.Include iron-rich foods (like spinach, lentils, and red meat) and vitamin C to boost absorption to help prevent this disease.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Scurvy -->
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Vitamin C Icon" />
    <h4>Avoid Scurvy</h4>
    <p>To prevent this disease include plenty of citrus fruits (oranges, lemons, limes), strawberries, kiwi, guava, bell peppers, broccoli, and tomatoes in your diet.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Rickets -->
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Sunlight Icon" />
    <h4>Prevent Osteomalacia</h4>
    <p>Spend time in sunlight regularly (about 10-30 minutes several times a week, depending on skin type and location).

Eat foods rich in vitamin D, such as fatty fish (salmon, mackerel), fortified dairy products, egg yolks, and mushrooms.</p>
  </div>

<div class="precaution-card">
      <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQGJ6US0RppXgOv9cGmBwmnTkzn5aIMHU-pHA&s" alt="Disinfection Icon" />
      <h4>Zinc Deficiency</h4>
      <p>Leads to: Growth retardation, impaired immunity, delayed wound healing

         Symptoms: Hair loss, poor appetite, skin lesions

         Sources: Meat, seafood, nuts, whole grains.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Lifestyle Diseases -->
<h3 class="precaution-group-title">Lifestyle Diseases</h3>
<div class="precautions-grid">
  <!-- Obesity -->
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Weight Scale Icon" />
    <h4>Hypertension</h4>
    <p>Cause by High salt (sodium) intake, Extra weight increases pressure on artery walls,Diets rich in saturated fats and cholesterol
Reduce salt (aim for < 5g/day), At least 30 minutes of moderate exercise most days of the week
Eat more fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean protein
 </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Liver Diseases -->
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Cholesterol Icon" />
    <h4>Liver Diseases</h4>
    <p>Viral infections (Hepatitis viruses), Excessive alcohol consumption ,Obesity and metabolic syndrome
Limit alcohol use, Maintain a healthy weight, Get vaccinated against hepatitis A and B, Avoid sharing needles or unprotected sex (to prevent hepatitis)
,Eat a balanced diet low in processed fats</p>
  </div>
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1683727186226-910f31a9da45?w=400&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8M3x8dHlwZSUyMDIlMjBkaWFiZXRlc3xlbnwwfHwwfHx8MA%3D%3D" alt="Migraine Icon" />
    <h4>Type 2 Diabetes</h4>
    <p>Monitor Lifestyle changes (diet and exercise), Oral medications or insulin therapy if prescribed, Monitoring blood glucose levels, Maintain a healthy weight

Eat a balanced diet rich in whole grains, vegetables, and lean proteins, Exercise regularly (at least 150 minutes per week)
Avoid excessive sugar and processed foods, Monitor blood sugar if you have risk factors, Managing blood pressure and cholesterol</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Migraine -->
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Migraine Icon" />
    <h4>Migraines</h4>
    <p>Migraines are intense, often debilitating headaches usually accompanied by symptoms such as nausea, vomiting, and sensitivity to light and sound.To avoid having this disease stay hydrated, avoid triggers like bright lights or skipped meals, and manage stress levels.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Chronic Conditions -->
<h3 class="precaution-group-title">Chronic Conditions</h3>
<div class="precautions-grid">
  <!-- Respiratory -->
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Blood Pressure Icon" />
    <h4>Respiratory Diseases</h4>
    <p>Asthma, Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD), Pneumonia, Tuberculosis (TB) are all common lung diseases.
precautions include quitting smoking or avoiding exposure to smoke, Use protective equipment if working in polluted environments
Exercise regularly to strengthen lungs, Vaccinate against flu and pneumonia, Manage asthma/allergies effectively
</p></div>
  <!-- Heart Disease -->
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Heart Icon" />
    <h4>Cardiovascular Diseases</h4>
    <p>Coronary Artery Disease (CAD),Heart Attack (Myocardial Infarction), Heart Failure, Arrhythmia are common heart diseases.</p>
  Eat a heart-healthy diet (fruits, veggies, whole grains, low sodium)
Preventions include getting regular physical activity (at least 30 mins/day), Maintain a healthy weight, Manage stress, Control blood pressure, cholesterol, and diabetes, Limit alcohol and processed foods,Get regular check-ups</div>

  <!--Autoimmune Diseases-->
  <div class="precaution-card">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Diabetes Icon" />
    <h4>Autoimmune Diseases</h4>
    <p>Here are precautions and preventive strategies for autoimmune diseases, which can help manage risk, reduce flare-ups, or delay disease progression:Choose whole, unprocessed foods: fruits, vegetables, nuts, seeds, lean proteins.
Avoid: processed foods, refined sugars, saturated fats, and artificial additives.Consider gluten- or dairy-free diets if sensitive (e.g., celiac or lupus patients)..</p>
  </div>
  <!-----Infections----->
<div class="precaution-card">
<img src="https://plus.unsplash.com/premium_photo-1679860817897-f539d0da8094?fm=jpg&q=60&w=3000&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8MXx8aW5mZWN0aW91cyUyMGRpc2Vhc2V8ZW58MHx8MHx8fDA%3D" alt="Hand Wash Icon" />
<h4>Infectious Diseases</h4>
<p>Influenza (Flu), COVID-19, Hepatitis A, B, C,Measles are infectious diseases.
precautions include:
Regularly wash your hands with soap and water to reduce germ transmission, Wear face masks in crowded places or during outbreaks.
Cover mouth and nose when sneezing or coughing.Avoid sharing personal items.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</body>
</html>


